<dl id="n12084j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12084j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12084j"> 84(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Le P&egrave;re Hyacinthe (Loyson) / Houtin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Le P&egrave;re Hyacinthe</b> Of what value is faith in the modern world? This is the question put to us, if only implicitly, by M. Albert Houtin&apos;s Life of Charles Loyson, <cite>Le p&egrave;re Hyacinthe</cite>. <small> <a name="CRII" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CRII"><cite title="source">The Criterion</cite></a>, II, VIII (July 1924)</cite></a> 461</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Albert Houtin: <cite>Le p&egrave;re Hyacinthe, pr&ecirc;tre solitaire</cite>, Paris 1924. Father Hyacinthe Loyson, French preacher (1827-1912). He opposed the dogma of the infallibility of the Pope and left the Catholic church to found a Gallican church. </mm> </dd></dl>
